      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDEN LOOM (6) in career best form in town and on the provincial tracks. Just over three-weeks between runs when he failed to close off with the 59kg to run seventh over 1600m at Newcastle. Will appreciate the 56kg here and assess on the good earlier runs in the city. DARK VADOR (5) has a solid record over this track and trip and stays in the mix with the dominant victory over 1625m at Wyong. Stalks the speed and gets his chance. Go close. INSTEAD (7) in career best form with the two wins from her last four runs. Motored late from back in the field with an eye catching third over 1600m at Tamworth. Key jockey change and look for her late from the inside gate. ONEFORIAN (8) just over five-weeks between runs when he knocked up late to finish seventh over 1600m at Canberra. Fitter now and not without top-three claims.",
